{"article_id":"zpsS2ZxaIQAfFncz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Facebook Inc. is taking steps","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"to address its role","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"in spreading fake news ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"such as enlisting the help of third-party fact checkers","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"and posting warnings on dubious stories .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Chief Executive Officer Mark Zuckerberg on Friday responded to criticism","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"that Facebook ' s news feed rewarded false stories in the run-up to the U.S. presidential election ,","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"including a post","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"that said","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Donald Trump was endorsed by the Pope .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"\" Normally we wouldn ' t share specifics about our work in progress ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"but given the importance of these issues and the amount of interest in this topic ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"I want to outline some of the projects","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"we already have underway , \"","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Zuckerberg said on Facebook .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"\" We need to be careful not to discourage sharing of opinions","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"or mistakenly restricting accurate content .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"We do not want to be arbiters of truth ourselves ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"but instead rely on our community and trusted third parties . \"","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Facebook is exploring labeling stories","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that have been reported as false by third parties or the community","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"so people are warned","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"before they read or share them ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Zuckerberg said .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"The company also is working","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"to make it easier for people to report fake news ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"and improve technical systems","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"to better detect such articles .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Facebook is also turning outside its own organization for help .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"It will meet with journalists","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"to understand how they verify information ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"and is exploring partnerships with third-party fact-checking organizations .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"Zuckerberg also noted","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"that fake news was becoming a big business ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"and said","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"Facebook is looking for ways","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"to disrupt the economics of it .","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"His remarks come","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"just a few days after he said","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"it was \" crazy \" to think","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"that fake news on Facebook influenced the outcome of the election .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"He ' s also said","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"that more than 99 percent of the stories on Facebook are accurate .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"But the criticism of his handling of the issue mounted ,","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"and by the end of the week , even President Barack Obama was speaking about the negative effect of fake stories on social media .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"\" Some of these ideas will work well ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"and some will not , \"","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Zuckerberg wrote .","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"\" But I want you to know","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that we have always taken this seriously ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"we understand how important the issue is for our community","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"and we are committed to getting this right . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":103,"left":56,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":56,"left":0,"right":55,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":55,"left":53,"right":54,"relation":"elaborati